{{Other uses of|Liriope}}
In [[Greek mythology]], '''Liriopê''' ([[Ancient Greek]]: Λιριοπη) or '''Leiriopê''' (Ancient Greek: Λειριοπη) is a [[Boeotia]] [[naiad]] of [[Thespiae]], who was probably the daughter of one of the Boeotian or Phocian river gods. Liriope was raped by the river-god [[Cephissus (mythology)|Cephissus]], who was himself the son of [[Oceanus]] and [[Tethys (mythology)|Tethys]], and bore his son [[Narcissus (mythology)|Narcissus]].<ref>[[Ovid]], ''Metamorphoses'', 3. 340</ref>

